reviewText:
This game brings me back to the good old days when I finished gothic 1. Great game

Pros:
-> great storyline, I love games with this kind of adventure, the Nameless Hero running around the world, beating the  ♥♥♥♥  out of big creatures;
-> can't say that it's difficult, I beat the game on hard difficulty. Still you need a little bit of experience in this kind of RPGs;
-> the game is pretty old, but still has good graphics.

I recommend this game, 8/10

Played Risen a bit so far. And definitely like it.
The good:
- gameplay;
- battle system;
- crafting systems (alchemy, smithing, etc);
- visual effects (including weather);
- dialogs and journaling system;
The bad:
- no first-person view;
- the world is rather small (comparing to Elder Scroll series);

Played Risen a bit so far. And definitely like it.
The good:
- gameplay;
- battle system;
- crafting systems (alchemy, smithing, etc);
- visual effects (including weather);
- dialogs and journaling system;
The bad:
- no first-person view;
- the world is rather small (comparing to Elder Scroll series);

TL;DR:
+ great atmosphere;
+ pretty good fighting / leveling system;
+ quite big world worth of exploration;
- first half of game is interesting, second is linear af;
- world, even if quite big, isn't even worth of comparing to TES games maps;
- pretty boring at last hours of playing.

IMO worth of playing, that's how Gothic III should look like.
